  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facilitating access to clean and safe drinking water to conflict-affected communities in Idleb 2020 - 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GOAL proposes to support 16 Water Stations (WSs) managed by 3 Water Units (WUs) in Idleb Governorate to enhance their capacity to meet increased local water demand owing to population displacements, outlined in section 2 of this proposal. The aim of the action is to ensure access to reliable, safe and clean drinking water by conflict-affected communities including host and displaced populations in the northern sub-districts of Idleb Governorate. This will be done through infrastructure rehabilitation and repairs, training and coaching to WUs and subordinated WSs staff, and water quality management. Complementary to this, COVID-19 adapted hygiene promotion sessions and COVID-19 community led action (CLA) sessions will be carried out. The project is a continuation of the ongoing OCHA Syria Cross-border Humanitarian Fund (SCHF) funded project (TUR-19/3559/SA2/WASH/INGO/14498) that is currently due to end on 08 July, and is pending modification request approval for extension until 31 July 2020. 


The proposed action will enable approximately 180,369 people living in the targeted WSs&#x2019; catchment areas to regularly access adequate quantities of clean and safe drinking water, piped directly to households (HHs). Approximately 35 litres/person/day (LPD) will be pumped to HHs. This is in accordance with current WASH Cluster COVID-19 guidance. Additionally, 3,150 people attending GOAL distributions under other projects will be reached with COVID-19 adapted hygiene promotion sessions and 350 individuals will participate in COVID-19 CLA sessions through this action. In total 3,500 people will benefit from hygiene activities.


GOAL&#x2019;s wider WASH programme, including the current active version of the proposed project, has undergone an intensive COVID-19 preparation and adaption process that will enable GOAL to continue providing these essential WASH services in the case of a COVID-19 outbreak.</narrative>
  </description>
